                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;'><strong>1. Debt Consolidation Loan (DCL):</strong></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;'>This is offered by banks and financial institutions, a Debt Consolidation Loan is designed to help individuals consolidate multiple outstanding debts, such as credit card balances, personal loans or other forms of unsecured debts into a single loan with a lower interest rate. This can simplify the repayment process by consolidating all debts into a single monthly payment and reduce the overall interest paid. However, be mindful of any fees or charges associated with the debt consolidation process, and the penalty interest rate if you fail to make a payment.&nbsp;</p>
