                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;'>A balance transfer allows individuals to transfer outstanding balances from one or more high-interest credit cards to a new credit card or specific credit facility. The purpose is to take advantage of the promotional offers of lower or zero-interest rate to offer temporary relief and save on interest charges. However, do note that this is a temporary reprieve to your outstanding debt and to maximize the benefits, individuals should aim to pay off the transferred balances within the promotional period to avoid higher interests later on.&nbsp;</p>
